    "question_id": "PG-1",
    "framework": "CAIQ",
    "text": "Are audit and assurance policies established, documented, and approved?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "Yes. BNY's Audit Committee has established pre-approval policies and procedures applicable to all services provided by the firm's independent registered public accountants, with two SEC-aligned approaches\u2014class pre-approval and specific pre-approval\u2014governing audit and permitted non-audit services. These policies are documented in BNY's Audit and Permitted Non-Audit Services Pre-Approval Policy, a copy of which is made available on the company's website, and they are approved by the Audit Committee (or its delegate). Operating on behalf of the Board, the Audit Committee oversees a comprehensive system of internal controls covering the integrity of financial statements and reports, compliance with laws, regulations and corporate policies, and the qualifications, performance and independence of the independent registered public accounting firm. The effectiveness of the framework is reflected in pre-approval coverage of 100% of fees associated with independent registered public accounting firm services for the most recently reported year.",
